File: lichen/subsys/lichen/senml/senml.c
Lines: 175-189

CATEGORY: CORRECTNESS

The encode_record() function calculates the number of map entries BEFORE validation:

  size_t entries = 1; /* value always present */
  if (is_first && pack->base_name != NULL) entries++;
  if (is_first && pack->has_base_time) entries++;
  if (rec->name != NULL) entries++;
  if (rec->unit != NULL) entries++;
  if (rec->has_time) entries++;

  if ((is_first && validate_name(pack->base_name) < 0) ||
      validate_name(rec->name) < 0 ||
      validate_unit(rec->unit) < 0) {
      return -EMSGSIZE;
  }

  if (!zcbor_map_start_encode(state, entries)) {

The validation at lines 182-186 returns -EMSGSIZE but this is after entries were counted assuming strings are valid. This is actually OK since validation returns before encoding starts.

However, there's a deeper issue: if base_name is non-NULL but ONLY contains whitespace/invalid chars (passes length check), and if RFC 8428 naming rules were ever enforced, the count would be committed but encoding might fail.

Actually, reviewing more carefully - this path returns error before encoding, so map is never started. This is not a bug.

Retracting this issue - let me find a real one instead.
